text:
Ravi Murdianto (born 8 January 1995) is an Indonesian professional &lt;a href="association%20football"&gt;footballer&lt;/a&gt; who plays as a &lt;a href="Goalkeeper%20%28association%20football%29"&gt;goalkeeper&lt;/a&gt;. He is also a &lt;a href="Sergeant%23Indonesia"&gt;second sergeant&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href="Indonesian%20Army"&gt;Indonesian Army&lt;/a&gt;.
Club career.
Ravi was born in &lt;a href="Grobogan%20Regency"&gt;Grobogan Regency&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="Central%20Java"&gt;Central Java&lt;/a&gt;. In childhood, Ravi joined to SSB Putra Bersemi. At that time, he did not become a &lt;a href="Goalkeeper%20%28association%20football%29"&gt;goalkeeper&lt;/a&gt;, but as a &lt;a href="midfielder"&gt;midfielder&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="Striker%20%28association%20football%29"&gt;striker&lt;/a&gt;. However, since the fourth grade of elementary school, Ravi becomes as a Goalkeeper. Posture is pretty high is a main factor. after the sixth grade elementary school, Ravi joined to SSB Tugumuda Semarang to get good training. When a teenager, Ravi successfully passed the selection in Diklat Salatiga. Two years later, Ravi joined to Diklat Ragunan. And the name of Ravi Murdianto getting famous. He was selected in &lt;a href="Indonesia%20national%20under-17%20football%20team"&gt;Indonesia U-17&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="Indonesia%20national%20under-19%20football%20team"&gt;Indonesia U-19&lt;/a&gt;
And then, Ravi joined to &lt;a href="Perserang%20Serang"&gt;Perserang Serang&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href="Liga%20Indonesia%20First%20Division"&gt;Liga Nusantara&lt;/a&gt;
International career.
Since Ravi was selected in Indonesia U-17 and U-19 team, Ravi's role as a main goalkeeper in the junior national team is irreplaceable. Along with the Indonesian national team U-17 and U-19 Indonesia, he won in the HKFA Tournament in &lt;a href="Hong%20Kong"&gt;Hong Kong&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="2013%20AFF%20U-19%20Youth%20Championship"&gt;2013 AFF U-19 Youth Championship&lt;/a&gt;
